did.physdesc:
TsS, 12 p., includes ms corrections;
                  includes carbon typescript, 9 p. with
                  corrections

scopecontent.p:
Likes all really bitter attacks, particularly one
                  in 
                  Saturday Review;
                  writes, "A vulgar, blatant scream" is not so bad;
                  mentions the 50 reviews he has from England, some of
                  which are very negative.

Writes that he had not planned on permanently
                  leaving New York when he departed on October 1;
                  discusses living in Los Angeles.

Explains that various other duties caused him to
                  forget conference with Dodd, Mead, and Liveright;
                  requests a few days notice for a talk.

Sends 25 of his 200 poems; offers to show others;
                  requests that those not chosen be promptly returned
                  as his poems are to be put into book form.

Writes that he and Helen have decided on winter
                  Thursdays to gather the 7 arts and 9 professions;
                  invites him.

Expresses interest in his letter; explains that he
                  did not contribute $.75 to the $300,000 fortune;
                  thanks him for his comments.

Thanks her for tickets and send payment for them;
                  hopes to go, but doesn't know if he will be able
                  to.
